author: @austin.luther
text:
This is fantastic. And you nailed it! I'm a trans man and I don't give a fuck what cis people call themselves. And if you misgender me, that's fine as long as you're cool with being gently corrected. I just started working at a new lab last year and it happened a few times and IT WASN'T A BIG DEAL. It's like getting someone's name wrong. No biggie, just don't be surprised when they correct you. 

"Hey, Larry." "Lenny." "Right, Lenny, sorry. So about the-"

See? Not hard. We do this all the time. And even misgendering is not new. The right just love themselves some patriarchy and that's a very bio-essentialist worldview with a strict hierarchy. Trans people threaten that. Our very existence is a dismissal of bio-essenstialist thinking.
